section.t:
Such a generic CPP template: Facilitates the automation of the service negotiation and activation procedures, thus improving service delivery times;
Can help set Traffic Engineering function and service management function objectives, for example, as a function of the number of CPP templates to be processed over a specific period of time; and
Improves service and network management systems by adding 'decision-making' capabilities based upon negotiated/offered CPPs.

Distinct treatments may be implemented for elastic and non-elastic
        traffic (e.g., see the "Constraints on traffic" clause defined in
        ).
